How to Use NETRA
NETRA is a command-line interface (CLI) tool. All commands follow the structure: python3 netra.py <command> <options>. Most wireless functions require Root privileges (sudo).

1. SCAN Mode: Network Reconnaissance
Use the scan command for multi-threaded port scanning, banner grabbing, and device fingerprinting.

Command Syntax	Purpose	Example
python3 netra.py scan -t <IP>	Basic scan of default ports.	python3 netra.py scan -t 192.168.1.1
sudo python3 netra.py scan -t <IP> -i <IFACE>	Full scan with MAC/Vendor discovery (Recommended).	sudo python3 netra.py scan -t 10.0.0.5 -i eth0
python3 netra.py scan -t <IP> --ports <LIST>	Scan a custom range/list of ports.	python3 netra.py scan -t 10.1.1.20 --ports 21,80,443,1000-2000
2. WIRELESS Mode: Attack & Utilities (Requires SUDO)
These commands interact directly with your Wi-Fi interface and require Monitor Mode for advanced functions.

Command Syntax	Purpose	Notes
sudo python3 netra.py wireless netscan -i <IFACE>	Performs an ARP scan of the local network.	
sudo python3 netra.py wireless deauth -i <MON_IF> -t <CLIENT_MAC> -g <AP_MAC>	Sends Deauth packets to disconnect a client.	Use -t FF:FF:FF:FF:FF:FF for broadcast.
sudo python3 netra.py wireless fake-ap -i <MON_IF> --ssid <NAME> -ch <CH>	Creates a Rogue AP (Requires airbase-ng). Interface auto-cleanup on exit.	Press Ctrl+C to stop the AP.
3. ATTACK Mode: Advanced Wi-Fi Attacks (v1.0)
New in v1.0, this mode provides enhanced attack capabilities with evasion techniques.

Command Syntax	Purpose	Example
sudo python3 netra.py attack deauth -i <MON_IF> -t <CLIENT_MAC> -g <AP_MAC>	Send deauth packets with evasion.	sudo python3 netra.py attack deauth -i wlan0mon -t 00:11:22:33:44:55 -g 66:77:88:99:AA:BB --evasion randomize
sudo python3 netra.py attack fakeap -i <MON_IF> --ssid <NAME> -ch <CH>	Create fake AP with customization.	sudo python3 netra.py attack fakeap -i wlan0mon --ssid "Free WiFi" --hidden --auth wpa2
4. SESSION Mode: Attack Sessions (v1.0)
Manage attack sessions for long-running operations.

Command Syntax	Purpose	Example
python3 netra.py session new --name <NAME> --config <FILE>	Create new attack session.	python3 netra.py session new --name "Test Session" --config config.json
python3 netra.py session save	Save current session to disk.	
python3 netra.py session load <FILE>	Load session from file.	python3 netra.py session load session_abc123.json
5. UTILS Mode: System Utilities
Command Syntax	Purpose	Example
sudo python3 netra.py utils mac-change -i <IFACE>	Changes interface MAC to a random address.	sudo python3 netra.py utils mac-change -i wlan0
python3 netra.py utils links	Displays helpful external resources and links.	
Installation Requirements
bash
Download
Copy code
# Install dependencies
pip3 install scapy
apt-get install -y aircrack-ng iwconfig ifconfig
Running NETRA
bash
Download
Copy code
# Basic usage
python3 netra.py scan -t 192.168.1.1

# With root privileges
sudo python3 netra.py wireless netscan -i wlan0mon
Advanced Usage Examples
1. Advanced Deauth Attack with Evasion
bash
Download
Copy code
sudo python3 netra.py attack deauth -i wlan0mon -t FF:FF:FF:FF:FF:FF -g 00:11:22:33:44:55 --evasion randomize rate_limit
2. Create Hidden Fake AP with WPA2 Protection
bash
Download
Copy code
sudo python3 netra.py attack fakeap -i wlan0mon --ssid "Corporate WiFi" --hidden --auth wpa2 --password "Secure123!"
3. Long-running Session Management
bash
Download
Copy code
# Start session
python3 netra.py session new --name "Weekend Test" --config config.json

# Run multiple attacks
sudo python3 netra.py attack deauth -i wlan0mon -t 00:11:22:33:44:55 -g 66:77:88:99:AA:BB
sudo python3 netra.py attack fakeap -i wlan0mon --ssid "Public WiFi" --auth open

# Save session
python3 netra.py session save
Security Considerations
All wireless attacks require Monitor Mode (sudo python3 netra.py utils mode -i wlan0 -m Monitor)
Session data is automatically saved for later analysis
Interface states are automatically restored after attacks
Logs provide detailed attack information for post-analysis
Development Status
This toolkit is in active development and may receive updates. For feature requests or bug reports, please open an issue on GitHub.

